description.google_ads: Not required. You can provide your own developer token with your custom client.
Your company's name in your Google Ads client application.

We use a Fivetran developer token to access the Google Ads API. If this is your first Google Ads connector with custom authorization, you should create a new Google API Console project. Each Google API Console project can be associated with the developer token from only one manager account. Once you make a Google Ads API request, the developer token is permanently paired to the Google API Console project. Otherwise, we can't bind the Fivetran developer token to your client. You can reuse the same project to create other Google Ads connectors. You can use your own developer token with your custom client if you have one, but it's not required
